    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>All examples use finite distributions with explicit probabilities. The paper's theorem holds over FinProb (finite probability distributions with morphisms that preserve total mass). The uniqueness result requires all three axioms — dropping any one allows other measures. Every example is <strong class="text-green-400">Simplified</strong>: the structure is preserved, the measure-theoretic generality is not.</p>

